# PromptForge: Product Plan v2.0 - Changes & Updates

**Document Type:** Product Plan Revision  
**Version:** 2.0 (Updated after Competitive Analysis & Architecture Review)  
**Date:** November 6, 2025  
**Status:** REVISED - Ready for Implementation

---

## üìã Executive Summary of Changes

This document outlines **key changes** to the original PromptForge product plan based on:
1. Competitive analysis of Gumroad PM Prompt Library ($49)
2. Review of claude-code-templates architecture
3. Integration of Claude Code's subagents and plugins capabilities

### High-Level Changes

| Category | Change Type | Impact |
|----------|------------|--------|
| **Distribution Model** | MAJOR | Added plugin-based distribution |
| **Architecture** | MAJOR | Added subagents for enhancement |
| **User Experience** | MODERATE | Added CLI installer & web browser |
| **Marketing** | MODERATE | Improved positioning vs. Gumroad |
| **Timeline** | MINOR | +4 days to Sprint 0 (now 10 days) |
| **Total Timeline** | MINOR | 7 weeks ‚Üí ~8 weeks |

---

## üéØ Section 1: Architecture Changes

### ORIGINAL: Skills-First + Pure Markdown

```
promptforge/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ .claude/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ skills/
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ promptforge/
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ SKILL.md
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ claude.md
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ prompts/
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ [70 prompt files]
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ docs/
```

**Distribution:** Git clone

### ‚úÖ REVISED: Plugin-Based with Subagents

```
promptforge-plugin/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ .claude-plugin/
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ plugin.json              # ‚ú® NEW: Plugin metadata
‚îÇ
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ skills/
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ promptforge/
‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ SKILL.md
‚îÇ
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ agents/                       # ‚ú® NEW: Subagents directory
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ prompt-enhancer.md       # ‚ú® NEW: Enhancement specialist
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ prompt-researcher.md     # ‚ú® NEW: Search & discovery
‚îÇ
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ commands/                     # ‚ú® NEW: Custom slash commands
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ prompt-browse.md
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ prompt-enhance.md
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ prompt-score.md
‚îÇ
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ prompts/
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ [70 prompt files]
‚îÇ
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ docs/
```

**Distribution:** Plugin marketplace (one-command install)

### Why This Change?

**Problem Solved:**
- Git clone is developer-focused, not PM-focused
- No auto-updates or version management
- Team adoption requires manual coordination

**New Benefits:**
- ‚úÖ One-command installation: `/plugin install promptforge`
- ‚úÖ Auto-updates when new prompts released
- ‚úÖ Team sharing via repository settings
- ‚úÖ Professional, polished distribution

