## üîå Section 3: NEW - Plugin Distribution

### Plugin Manifest

**New File:** `.claude-plugin/plugin.json`

```json
{
  "name": "promptforge",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "World-class Product Manager prompt library with AI-powered enhancement",
  "author": "PromptForge Team",
  "license": "MIT",
  "homepage": "https://github.com/promptforge/plugin",
  "repository": "https://github.com/promptforge/plugin",
  "keywords": ["prompts", "product-management", "pm", "enhancement"],
  "components": {
    "skills": ["promptforge"],
    "agents": ["prompt-enhancer", "prompt-researcher"],
    "commands": ["prompt-browse", "prompt-score", "prompt-validate"]
  },
  "requirements": {
    "claude-code": ">=1.0.0"
  }
}
```

### Marketplace Distribution

**New File:** `marketplace.json`

```json
{
  "name": "PromptForge Marketplace",
  "description": "Official PromptForge plugin marketplace",
  "plugins": [
    {
      "name": "promptforge",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "source": "https://github.com/promptforge/plugin",
      "description": "Complete PM prompt library with 70+ world-class prompts"
    }
  ]
}
```

### Installation Experience

**OLD (Git Clone):**
```bash
# User has to:
cd ~/projects
git clone https://github.com/promptforge/library.git
cd library
# Now what? Manual setup? Configuration?
```

**NEW (Plugin):**
```bash
# User does:
/marketplace add promptforge
/plugin install promptforge
# Done! Everything works automatically
```

### Team Distribution

**NEW: Repository-Level Configuration**

Teams can add to `.claude/settings.json`:

```json
{
  "marketplaces": [
    "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/promptforge/marketplace/main/marketplace.json"
  ],
  "plugins": ["promptforge"]
}
```

**Result:** When team members trust the folder, PromptForge auto-installs!

### Update Mechanism

**OLD:**
```bash
# User has to remember to:
cd ~/projects/promptforge
git pull
```

**NEW:**
```bash
# Automatic update notifications:
"New PromptForge version available (1.0.0 ‚Üí 1.1.0)"
/plugin update promptforge
```

