## üåê Section 5: NEW - Web Interface & CLI

### Inspired by claude-code-templates

Original plan had no web interface. Now adding:

#### CLI Tool (npx package)

**New Package:** `promptforge` on npm

**Usage:**
```bash
# Interactive browser
npx promptforge@latest

# One-command setup (creates marketplace, installs plugin)
npx promptforge@latest --install

# Update to latest
npx promptforge@latest --update

# Browse specific category
npx promptforge@latest --category research

# Show stats
npx promptforge@latest --stats

# Validate setup
npx promptforge@latest --validate
```

#### Web Browser (GitHub Pages)

**New Site:** `promptforge.dev` (or GitHub Pages)

**Features:**
- Browse all 70 prompts online
- Filter by: category, CLEAR score, time estimate, industry
- Search bar (client-side, instant)
- View full prompt with metadata
- Copy to clipboard buttons
- Link to plugin installation
- Real-time stats (most popular prompts)

**Why This Matters:**
- Discovery without installing anything
- SEO benefits (Google can index prompts)
- Shareable links to specific prompts
- Professional web presence
- Marketing tool

#### Analytics Dashboard

**New Command:** `npx promptforge@latest --stats`

**Shows:**
- Which prompts you've used (local tracking)
- Average CLEAR score improvements from enhancements
- Estimated time saved
- Most-used categories
- Enhancement usage patterns

**Privacy:** All stats local, no telemetry sent

